    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter #33889, `.nvim.lua` startup scripts from parent directories are loaded via a `VimEnter` autocmd after the `FileType` event, unlike script in the current directory which are sourced earlier by `source_startup_scripts` function. This causes project-specific configurations, such as LSP settings, to be applied too late when nvim is started from a subdirectory, resulting in inconsistent behavior.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nTo reproduce this issue, modify the `init.lua` file rather than using the '-u' option. nvim [does not load exrc scripts](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/78f4994627b7d9c3b85f30028fe55ff38024a39d/src/nvim/main.c#L2104-L2119) when this option is selected.\n\ninit.lua:\n```lua\nvim.lsp.config('clangd', {cmd={'clangd'},filetypes={'c'}})\nvim.lsp.enable('clangd')\nvim.opt.exrc = true\n```\n\nCreate the .nvim.rc file and `:trust`\n```lua\nvim.lsp.config(\"clangd\", {\n  cmd = { \"clangd\", \"--background-index\" },\n})\n```\n\nRun `nvim main.c` to launch neovim, then verify that the LSP configuration changes in `.nvim.lua` have been applied.\n```lua\nvim.lsp.get_clients({bufnr=0, name=\"clangd\"})[1].config.cmd\n-- result: { \"clangd\", \"--background-index\" }  \n```\n\nRun neovim in a subdirectory.\n```sh\nmkdir subdir\ncd subdir\nnvim main.c\n```\nAlthough the configuration had been loaded, it had not been applied in time for the server to use it.\n```lua\nvim.lsp.config.clangd.cmd\n-- result: { \"clangd\", \"--background-index\" } \nvim.lsp.get_clients({bufnr=0, name=\"clangd\"})[1].config.cmd\n-- result: { \"clangd\" }  \n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe .nvim.lua scripts in parent directories are sourced at the same stage as those in the current directory.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-926+g78f4994627\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narchlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
